  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across five flow-speed combinations. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated; seven received full assessment narratives with documented rationale. The assessment team judged that convergent evidence across validation activities, combined with conservative UQ bounds, supported a Medium assurance level. Decision: Accepted. NOTE (adversarial): assuranceLevel 'Medium' is inconsistent with the structural evidence — at least one factor has achievedLevel strictly below requiredLevel in an Accepted decision, triggering W-AR-02 and COMPOUND-03.",
