    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that the aggregate credibility evidence supports a Medium assurance level for the VAD hemolysis prediction. Seven of thirteen factors were fully assessed; convergent validation evidence across PIV and in vitro hemolysis data, combined with Monte Carlo UQ bounds bracketing four of five experimental observations, was judged sufficient to accept the model for COU2 decision support. Acknowledged gaps in discretization error (GCI 6.2% vs 5% threshold), numerical solver convergence at one operating point, and model form sensitivity were characterized as manageable within the UQ envelope. The team exercised engineering judgment that these gaps, while present, did not individually or collectively invalidate the Medium assurance determination. Two unassessed factors (test samples, equivalency of input parameters) were noted as epistemic gaps to be addressed in subsequent assessment cycles.",
